 should be examined more critically for their continued importance, and additional theorists thus far neglected should complement them. Each chapteris organized as a debate between two theorists with contrasting views and approaches. At the end of each chapter, there is a critical evaluation of these political theorists’ continued or renewed relevance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 4aCoursebook. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh1 aAlthusius, Hobbes V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAristotle, Plato V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarsilius, Thomas V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarx, Nietzsche V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMontesquieu, Locke V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrince, Machiavelli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRousseau, Wollstonecraft, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTocqueville, Rousseau V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVico, Descartes V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWollstonecraft, Burke V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144260684540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442606845423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781442606845/original  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_E